- '1080p' refers to the resolution of the video, indicating high definition (HD) quality; 
- '2023' specifies the year of video upload; 
- 'L1' or 'color intensity' could refer to a measure of the brightness or saturation of colors in the ROI; 
- 'ROI' stands for Region of Interest, which could be an area within the video that is of particular importance or focus.

- 'Popular videos' refers to the videos with the highest access counts; 
- 'Most frequent viewers' are the users who accessed each video the most number of times; 
- 'Regions of interest' (ROIs) are specific areas within the videos that have been marked as significant; 
- 'Average metrics' (L1, L2, L3) refer to the average values of certain metrics (e.g., color intensity, motion vector, object detection score) associated with each ROI.
